
[1]eolipile

   EOL'IPILE, n. [Aeolus, the deity of the winds, and pila, a ball.]

   A hollow ball of metal, with a pipe or slender neck, used in hydraulic
   experiments. The ball being filled with water, is heated, till the
   vapor issued from the pipe with great violence and noise, exhibiting
   the elastic power of steam.
